[
    {
        "content": "<p>Do we have composition of formal power series yet (under suitable conditions)? Or, what is more or less the same thing, evaluation at elements in the maximal ideal of a complete local ring?</p>",
        "id": 211990802,
        "sender_full_name": "Reid Barton",
        "timestamp": 1601597023
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Can I define a <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Formal_group_law\">formal group law</a>--roughly, a power series <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>F</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>X</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>Y</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>∈</mo><mi>R</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">[</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">[</mo><mi>X</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>Y</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">]</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">]</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">F(X, Y) \\in R[[X, Y]]</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.22222em;\">Y</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">∈</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.00773em;\">R</span><span class=\"mopen\">[</span><span class=\"mopen\">[</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.22222em;\">Y</span><span class=\"mclose\">]</span><span class=\"mclose\">]</span></span></span></span> of the form <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>F</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>X</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>Y</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>X</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>Y</mi><mo>+</mo><mo>⋯</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">F(X, Y) = X + Y + \\cdots</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.22222em;\">Y</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.76666em;vertical-align:-0.08333em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.76666em;vertical-align:-0.08333em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.22222em;\">Y</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.31em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\">⋯</span></span></span></span> satisfying <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>F</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>F</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>X</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>Y</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>Z</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>F</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>X</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>F</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>Y</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>Z</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">F(F(X, Y), Z) = F(X, F(Y, Z))</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.22222em;\">Y</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">Z</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.22222em;\">Y</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">Z</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>?</p>",
        "id": 211990907,
        "sender_full_name": "Reid Barton",
        "timestamp": 1601597091
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I know we have <code>analysis.analytic.composition</code> so we must have something in this area but it's a bit intimidating and I didn't immediately find anything like <code>mv_power_series.eval</code> or <code>.comp</code>.</p>",
        "id": 211991370,
        "sender_full_name": "Reid Barton",
        "timestamp": 1601597523
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Analytic functions are based on <code>multilinear_function</code>s, not <code>mv_power_series</code>.</p>",
        "id": 211997694,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1601604997
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>AFAIK, we don't have the composition of <code>(mv_)power_series</code> yet.</p>",
        "id": 211997704,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1601605022
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"110032\">@Reid Barton</span> Nope, we don't have these yet... sorry</p>",
        "id": 212008360,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1601618991
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Does this outline sound correct? Given an <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>R</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">R</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.00773em;\">R</span></span></span></span>-algebra <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">A</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span></span></span></span> which is a complete local ring and elements <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>y</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mo>…</mo><mo>∈</mo><mi>A</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">x, y, \\ldots \\in A</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7335400000000001em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">y</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\">…</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">∈</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span></span></span></span> belonging to the maximal ideal, define the evaluation of a formal power series <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>F</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi>R</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">[</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">[</mo><mi>X</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>Y</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mo>…</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">]</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">]</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">F \\in R[[X, Y, \\ldots]]</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.72243em;vertical-align:-0.0391em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">∈</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.00773em;\">R</span><span class=\"mopen\">[</span><span class=\"mopen\">[</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.22222em;\">Y</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\">…</span><span class=\"mclose\">]</span><span class=\"mclose\">]</span></span></span></span> at <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>y</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mo>…</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">x, y, \\ldots</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">y</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\">…</span></span></span></span>. Then prove the power series ring is itself such an algebra whose maximal ideal consists of the power series with 0 leading term.</p>",
        "id": 212231371,
        "sender_full_name": "Reid Barton",
        "timestamp": 1601831206
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Are those the right hypotheses? Do we have these concepts in mathlib yet?</p>",
        "id": 212231384,
        "sender_full_name": "Reid Barton",
        "timestamp": 1601831224
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You don't need local. If J is an ideal of the R-algebra A and A is J-adically separated and complete (a concept which we might not have -- but which we used in the perfectoid project so will be around somewhere -- it just means that A to projlim A/J^n is an iso) then you can evaluate power series at elements of J</p>",
        "id": 212240989,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1601844257
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Probably in the perfectoid project we had the concept of the J-adic topology on A and the notion of the corresponding uniform space being complete and separated but now there might be some work defining that power series map</p>",
        "id": 212241087,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1601844396
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"110032\">@Reid Barton</span>  I think we have all what <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"110038\">@Kevin Buzzard</span> is talking about in mathlib now. Thanks to <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"110064\">@Kenny Lau</span> who added J-adic stuff.</p>",
        "id": 212241319,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1601844785
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>/me feels like a person in a foreign country. I hope, after someone formalizes this, we'll have <code>mv_power_series.comp (f g : mv_power_series σ R)</code> that gives what everybody expects (if <code>g</code> has a non-zero constant coeff, then <code>comp</code> can either return zero, or silently subtract this constant first).</p>",
        "id": 212241674,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1601845330
    }
]